    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-18T03:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-18T03:30:00-05:00" n="370"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d370">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">689.90D/12–1851: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Horner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kabul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-18T13:00:00+04:30"
                            >December 18, 1951—1 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>290. We wish to reiterate our belief that progress can be made in settling
                        Afghan–<gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> differences if we take advantage
                    now of evident Afghan desire find face-saving formula. Vital point in <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 250 is achievement one or more year’s
                    moratoruim on all Pashtun propaganda or vituperative press and radio exchanges;
                    we believe that Pashtun campaign, once buried, wld be difficult if not
                    impossible to dig up again (<gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss> is far too
                    astute not to have realized this when he made his suggestion reported in <gloss
                        target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 231 of Nov 8). Since Dept expresses
                    reluctance to have US give written assurance that Pashtun case will be given
                    hearing when world tension ceases we suggest possibility <gloss target="#t_GOP1"
                        >GOP</gloss> wld be willing give such written assurance which, however, <pb
                        facs="0539" n="2003" xml:id="pg_2003"/> wld have to bear endorsement of US,
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> or some third party in whom Afghans have
                    confidence.</p>
                <p>We wld appreciate Dept’s comments.</p>
                <p>Dept pass Karachi. Sent Dept 290; rptd info Karachi 47.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Horner</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
